  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Vasanta Sampat Dupare versus Union of India & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_8_2136_2182','2025INSC1043'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VASANTA SAMPAT DUPARE<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>UNION OF INDIA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 2136</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1043</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007612025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KAROL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Writ petition filed u/Art.32 challenging the continuing validity of the sentence of death against the petitioner, having been affirmed on appeal, declined in review, and followed by the rejection of mercy petitions and seeks its reconsideration in the light in the case of Manoj and others v. State of Madhya Pradesh; and whether Art.32 authorises this Court to reopen a capital sentencing exercise that has otherwise attained finality, solely to cure the procedural lapse the petitioner identifies. Headnotes&dagger; Constitution of India &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 25-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> WRIT PETITION (CRIMINAL) No. 371/2023</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','20